Tried squatting with a weightlifting belt for the first time in four years because people keep telling me how much safer it is and how I can get more reps on each set. I load 3 plates and on the first rep belt pops open and tears itself into two pieces. Almost fell crashing down.

Genuinely scary moment, could have dropped 315 lbs. on my head and neck, but I squat barefoot sol brah style (I just go barefoot around the gym because I'm too autistic to wear shoes) so my feet gripped the gym floor and I kept my balance. Going to try a belt again in 5 years. GG

The big paradox of lifting/natural bodybuilding is when you are a beginner literally nothing works, you can do any sort of variations/rep ranges and it's all meh, but when you have a ton of muscle mass "anything works" and you can get massive pumps doing girl dumbbells lat raises

Like triceps pushdowns. When ur a noob no matter what you do ur basically fucked. Struggling to balance the straight bar, can't move any weight w/ the rope attachment, etc. Then in a few years you push the entire stack, rope gives you brutal stretch. Ur literally Too big to fail.

I didn't really convey it well but for a few seconds I genuinely was convinced I was going mad and hallucinating people, the way the sun was reflecting in the seawater into my eyes and a silhouette emerged in the corner of my vision just felt very supernatural. Had fun time tho..
